## Architecture Comparison: EAM vs MPAS

EAM:
  horiz_remap_file(tape) -> cam_history accumulates on native grid
  -> dump_field applies remap at write time -> PIO writes to (lon,lat)
  -> SAME filename, SAME tape, transparent to user

MPAS:
  horiz_remap_file(AM) -> AM computes on native grid -> stores in pool
  -> stream manager writes native file (or skips if output_stream='none')
  -> SEPARATELY: AM remaps fields -> PIO writes to SEPARATE file

The difference is structural (stream manager limitation), not a bug.

